This PR adds support for django-CMS-3.4 and djangocms-text-ckeditor-3.1 and higher.
When merged it will trigger a version jumpt to 0.12.0.

@pcolmant please review it, since it is going to superseed your PR #210.

This merges back a number of (modified) patches by @torotil from his [fork](https://github.com/torotil/sqlalchemy-json). The changes include:

* Using the SQLAlchemy utils provided JSONType for better compatibility and completeness (this resolves #3);
* Updating lookup and iteration code to be Python3 compatible;
* Allow the top level container to be a `list` in addition to a `dict`.

brief example
```python
class A(HasTraits):
    i = Int()
    
    @default('x')
    def _x_default(self):
        return 1

A().i
```
result : `1`

This also fixes `README.rst` and removes `README.md`, so we only have a single Readme.

@andfoy, the problem with the **0.2.1** tarballs missing the server components was not your fault. It was an error in `SdistWithBuildStatic`.

Hopefully this PR will prevent that in the future.

